[h1]Comparison Operators[/h1]

Comparison operators are used in logical statements to determine equality or difference between variables or values. They return [b]true[/b] or [b]false[/b]. 

The [b]equal to (==)[/b] operator checks whether the operands' values are equal.[code format="js" codeId="656"]var num = 10; 
// num == 8 will return [b]false[/b][/code]
